  "grammar": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Grammar Spot",
      "content": "• Positive: He gets up early.\n• Negative: He doesn't get up late.\n• Question: What time does he get up?\n• Short answer: Yes, he does. / No, he doesn't.\n• Adverbs: usually (90%), sometimes (40%), never (0%)\n• I work / He works / She works"
    },
    "ja": {
      "title": "文法のポイント",
      "content": "• 肯定文: He gets up early.（彼は早く起きます。）\n• 否定文: He doesn't get up late.（彼は遅く起きません。）\n• 疑問文: What time does he get up?（彼は何時に起きますか？）\n• 短い答え: Yes, he does. / No, he doesn't.\n• 頻度の副詞: usually（たいてい 90%）、sometimes（時々 40%）、never（決して〜ない 0%）\n• I work / He works / She works"
    },
    "fr": {
      "title": "Point de Grammaire",
      "content": "• Positif: He gets up early.\n• Négatif: He doesn't get up late.\n• Question: What time does he get up?\n• Réponse courte: Yes, he does. / No, he doesn't.\n• Adverbes: usually (90%), sometimes (40%), never (0%)\n• I work / He works / She works"
    },
    "ko": {
      "title": "문법 포인트",
      "content": "• 긍정문: He gets up early. (그는 일찍 일어납니다.)\n• 부정문: He doesn't get up late. (그는 늦게 일어나지 않습니다.)\n• 의문문: What time does he get up? (그는 몇 시에 일어나나요?)\n• 짧은 답변: Yes, he does. / No, he doesn't.\n• 빈도 부사: usually (보통 90%), sometimes (가끔 40%), never (절대 ~하지 않다 0%)\n• I work / He works / She works"
    }
  },
